27 §2800.78. Liability for victims depicted in child sexual abuse materials; cause
28 of action; damages
29 A. The Legislature of Louisiana hereby finds and declares that it is
30 necessary to establish meaningful civil remedies to deter the exploitation of
31 minors depicted in child sexual abuse materials and to provide redress for the
32 ongoing and compounding harm caused to such children by the creation,
33 possession, and continued circulation of those materials.
34 B. A person who is a minor and who is harmed as a result of being
35 depicted in child sexual abuse material shall have a cause of action for damages
36 against any person that produces, promotes, advertises, distributes, possesses,
